<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uaach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 6:48:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> The sickening thing for me is Bard bots - they double up as enhance bots, heal bots, rez bots, runspeed bots and can escape with ease if threatened while on their own.  Three times I participated in killing a Hib gang who wind up with one archer left alive then: 'whizzz' a bard appears and resurects eveyone.  Then 'whizzz' they all zoom off to recuperate.<br>
<br>
Putting a range on buffs - even PK to MG - *is* a nerf of buff class (except Bards and to a lesser extend Healers).  Precisley because it prevents a buff class from assisting an assassin who is scouting the MG and *assisting* is what they do.<br>
<br>
Enhance spec charachters choose a class that is almost the exact oposite or the 'in your face' assassin.  Its a legitimate way to play the game and for them to pair up with an assassin or archer is ideal grouping.<br>
<br>
Debuffs are extreemly powerfull against buffs and debuffs are instacast and often AoE.  Buffs are crap in comparison to Debuffs (their counter).  So what If I survive 4 nukes (or arrows) instead of 3 that just means that the stun wears off a half second before I die (that assumes I didn't get insta debuffed).  I am no more capable of fighting a group and surviving, so it is not realy an aid to soloing except vs other soloists and (as has already been pointed out) play skill is far more important there.<br>
<br>
There is no way that the tiny minority of soloists should call for a nerf of a legitimate class and a legitmate play style.<br>
<br>
These 'dreadfull' people who have girlfriends or parents who don't (always) like the confrontational nature of PvP but want to participate in the hobby of their loved ones.  So they use their enhance skill to help and chat or go afk.<br>
<br>
These people have a right to play the game in this way - to make this playstyle unviable would be a travesty far worse than any of the nerfs to other classes.<br>
<br>
You demand the right to kill the buffer and that is simply not acceptable because it imposes your play style at the expense of theirs.  You *can* demand the right to be able to counteract the effect of the buffer but you already have that (mostly in your own class) by grouping with another debuff class.<br>
<br>
Introduce what would be, in effect, an RP penalty for people with buff bots by donating some RP you earn to anyone who buffed you.  Thats quite adequate to maintain all three styles of play, it penalises the buff maniacs sufficiently to discourage them and benefits the buff spec people who often need to 'cross buff' for efficiency. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/unage42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nage42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 6:54:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3701.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Infs and their BuffBot Hand jobs</span><hr size=1> Well, as hass been pointed out, buffbots are 000ber.<br>
